frog.misc

Class Wall

  • java.lang.Object
    • frog.misc.Wall

  • public class Wall
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a wall in the maze. Can be solid, have a doorway, or be completely empty.
    Author:
    Justin Hwang

    • Method Detail

      • getTileOnOtherSide

        public java.awt.Point getTileOnOtherSide(java.awt.Point p)
        Returns the Point of the tile on the opposite side of the wall. Returned Point (tile) may be out of bounds
        Returns:
        Point of the tile on opposite side of the wall as the given one. If the given one does not neighbor the wall, then null is returned.

      • getBothNeighbors

        public java.awt.Point[] getBothNeighbors()
        Returns two Points of tiles on either side of this wall. May be out of bounds.
        Returns:
        Array of two Points (always exactly 2 Points, no more, no less) of the neighboring tiles.

      • getRectangles

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.awt.Rectangle> getRectangles()
        Returns the Rectangles of this wall. If Wall is empty, no Rectangle. If solid, one Rectangle. If doorway, two Rectangles.
        Returns:
        ArrayList of Rectangles that represent this wall. Either nothing, one solid rectangle, or two partial rectangles.

      • getRectanglesWithoutConversion

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.awt.Rectangle> getRectanglesWithoutConversion()
        Returns the rectangles of this wall, without converting the points to pixel coords
        Preconditions:
        Assumes that wall is solid

      • wallCoordsToPixelCoords

        public static java.awt.Point wallCoordsToPixelCoords(double x,
                                                     double y)
        Returns Point that contains the pixel coordinates of the CENTER of the wall. NOT the upper left corner.
        Parameters:
        x - X-coordinate (in wall coords) of the wall
        y - Y-coordinate (in wall coords) of the wall
        Returns:
        Point containing pixel coordinates of the CENTER of the wall, NOT the upper left corner
